					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I believe the main compression gain provided by solid compression is when multiple files in the archive are similar, like the ROM sets that include every variant ever dumped, over/underdumps, bad dumps, etc, but the bulk of the files are identical, resulting in HUGE compression gains from solid archiving.  7z without solid compression is still better than zip on average, though I don't know off the top of my head by how much.</div>

