				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If the majority of the MSU-1 data is PCM, there's not much sense in using a general-purpose compressor.<br /><br />A quick test across a few audio files suggests that both zip (deflate) and 7z (LZMA2) typically hit around 90% of the original size, whereas FLAC compresses to around 60% and has the added benefit of allowing random access so that the whole track need not be decompressed at once.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

