						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">byuu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Whatever makes the audio sound good is the correct answer <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" /></div><br />If you don't define it could lead to edge cases where it sounds good in one emulator but not on the other.<br /><br />Suppose you are playing the same sample at the same time on both the s-dsp and the msu1, if one of the signals is negated it could cancel the other out.<br />So if you implement this differently it would be possible to create a game that has sound in no$sns but not in higan, even though both follows the specifications. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

